  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.3278" xml:lang="de">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <opener>Dear D<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi> Schuchardt,</opener>
        <p>I received on the 29<hi
            rendition="#sup">th</hi> of March 1893 10 copies of the first part of my Concordance to S<hi
            rendition="#sup">t</hi> Johns Epistles and immediately sent you one of them. Alas, I find two gross blunders and several others less important. These will be confessed in the concluding part of the work which will I hope be out in May. On page VII insert “sometimes” before <hi
            rend="unknown" rendition="#none">
change</hi> in the 4<hi
            rendition="#sup">th</hi> line. On page 2 line 9 instead of <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">Id quod préc</hi>. read “Ind: prés pl. 3<hi rendition="#sup">e</hi> r. pl. 2<hi
            rendition="#sup">e</hi> pers. <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">n</hi> relatif” and add “aux: act” after <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">ez.</hi> page 6 line 11 instead of imparf. s, read présent. s. <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">n</hi> rel. It is difficult to avoid mistakes in a work of this nature. Let me have your opinion on this specimen of my labours. You will I think be glad to hear that I have already corrected the proofs of my Concordance to Philemon and my copy of the Te Deum in Souletin as printed by Ressegue]s[ bestela Merci at <placeName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.121">Pau</placeName> in the last century. These opuscules will appear in a week or two in the quarterly publication of the <ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.subjects#S.4686">Société Ramond</ref> at Bagnères de Bigorre, and I shall have a tirage à part I think, by which you will profit. I walked from Séez to Alençon yesterday, lunching en route at <hi
            rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">Larré</hi>, where there are some good pastures. I leave Alençon on Saturday for Mortagne. I shall pass Sunday at Chartres and reach my room at Paris on the 10<hi
            rendition="#sup">th</hi>. Inchauspe revised my proofsheets but never noticed the mistakes which grieve me so deeply. Indeed my Bascological work meets with but little<note
            n="1" place="foot" type="editorial">Dodgson setzt am linken Rand fort.</note> encouragement.</p>
        <closer>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1402">E. S. Dodgson</persName>. </signed>
          <dateline>4 April 1893.</dateline>
        </closer>
        <pb facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/>
        <postscript>
          <p>Do <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">not</hi> return the proofsheet as I asked.</p>
        </postscript>
      </div>
    </body>
